TextBlock.TextLine: In Antwerpen 19 aprill
Dermond Malliart oft ene
Mons. tis nu seer nae 6 maenden geleden als wanneer aen ul
huysvrouwe verkoght hebbe een pertije goet volgens de facture aen ul
gesonden, te betalen sonder rabat in 4 a 5 maenden hebbe mijn goet
aen ul seer goede koop verkoght op hope vant continueeren ende dat
ul mij prompt soude hebbe voldaen, en tot mijn leet wesen, en hebbe sedert
van ul gelt noch persoon niet vernomen, alleen dat daer nae aen ul
ordre de 2 serges hebbe gesonden, soo danigh manieren van handelen en
kan niet vant prijsen, jae geloove dat en in sijn Eijgen gemoet wel kan
ordeelen, dat ick daer mede tekort kome, oversulx terwijlen nu
grootelijkx ben verlegen om gelt, soo bidde mij gelieft soo veelte
betaelen als immers mogelijck is waer op mij verlate & blijve
19 Aprill 1681
th
London Henry Collier
Sr my last to you wason the 15: curitt sence non from you, so this cleefly for
advise that I have this day drawne on you £45„ 18:4 utt one uso payable
ƒ
to the order of Peeter kesteman for the valew of Adriaen speecq att 35:1
which is £81:17:8 flemish, besides £100 st att 2 uso payable to
mr. Anneslay att 35:0 both which please to accept & pay accordingly &
pass to yd owne acctt. for I have payd this day the £200: bill of LK
of 41 feb for which I am not a forthing in cash in case m' annesley
should Desire from you ordemand about £42: st up on my onone
Jacctt. please to pay itt to him & rembourse yd self on mee attsight
one or 2 uso inclosed you have pattarnes for 6 or 8 spanish cloathes
which please to provide pr. first & send mee I have sold yeasterday &
of yd cloathes the last prove very Deare: I have nomore in large

butt that I ame
th
London Henry Maynard
S: my last to you was on the 15: curitt to which referre you some
have receaved yd of 4 ditto where by perceave that the bale N11 conne
to late to come ih muchiel De raes I tought as muchtbecause
he was arrived before had yd formar letter, I wonder that said bale was
not soones ready: whoever pray dispatch itt pr first & that good care
betaken to putt itt within the ship, for I had rather to be att the charge
of bringing itt up to london againe then to leave itt att grave sande
for thought the shippers do promise to take itt in, they will feuray
open the bale & full the faults of the ships with, biy which means
wee should be verij lijkelij to suffes, where fore pray take good care
& tell as much to mr. scawen, though I do not write to him this past
I observe the pack of Dozins to be aboard Richd. pindar the patt
& prijses do please, if the goods do prove accordingly, itt well
he to boath our advantage, our 2 sales fron costy & the one
from hull are well arrived att rotted am & long to see them hre
exspecting them next week, when I'll give you a better accompt
of the morthrens, whilst promtrim do send you here inclosed
pattarnes of our most demanded cloathes, which I resire may
serve you for ginde, to provide 2 bales each to cout ir panish
clout hes all modecolleurs, I send these pattarnes ovely that you
might see, what is most demanded here I will not tyd you up
to them, butt leave the makeing up of these 2 bales to yd faney, for
itt may be you will finde some to yd content, good icheap, not
much differing from the pattarnes onely that you wherefore
lett mee have good & substantiall goods & the best the markest
will afford, aroyd all threadbare & snelling goods each ball to
be vorappered with 4 bayes luy also without any loss of time 5 p
El yealam marck pack whites abbes you cn gett them
without any further adviser & Dispach them with allspeed inclosed
accompt of sale of last month now I hope to be a remitting hence
forward to yd content, haveing some mony already that plespose
& so remaine with kinde sallees
rr. Maynard thought these 12 pattarnes are of such cloathes as are here
demanded yett in case you can finde & meet with some, which are more
pleasant & lively & newermore, & lease to send them I want sever all
cloathes of 6 a 6:6 u yd thought itt should be 12 peeces to eac
putt, one provide them, and the rest from 9 st to 9 a 9:6 pence ayd
so referre you to yd self to do the best you can, for when goods wee
brought, ree can sll well lett non be of arising wool, butt good
in uall respecte
in Collier accordingly to these patt please to provide 6 or 8 spinitl
cloathes of 8 st to 12 st ayd butt rather non under 9, so in casse sou
mee them to content thought some drap collours more lidely
then these pattarnes buy them & exceed not the number & send
them buy non whoes wooll is arising non sappy, or stinking obottall
substantiall goods from 9 st ayd tto 2 st ayd tobe prest & don up as
the last
In Antwerpen 20 Aprill
Brussel Bernaerd vander klooster
mons. in antwoort aenden ul van 18 deser segge wat dat ul niet aen staet
vant gesonden goedt het selve in ul huys te bewaeren & niet in de halle
laete liggen & als ick overkom sal daer van dieponneeren Alsoo de bayen
opt minst sijn gestelt & noch minder als gisteren aen vrinden van brussel
hebbe verkoght & gesonden, die van 5A sijn al verkoght den gesonden
rooy lest deventer bay valt seer goede koop daer al buyten die put het
best salt konnen winnen als hij wat geve ul kanden selve doen snew
wit maken gelijk hier geschiet hebbe gisteren een pack ander deventer
bayen gecresen & het selve open gedaen, ende ul daer af een fijn stuck
gesonden & nu een andere bay gesonden

20 Aprill 1681
Brussel Joan Jacops
r

soorte dewelke ul vraghde doch hebbe van een ander meester een pack
oopen gedaen & daer uyt deminste soorte genomen, waer van ul gisteren
hebbe toegesonden in een pack IPS 13 stucken & fijn vant merck
N & RA Door a 13 stucken a
wille niet twijffelen oft de selve sullen ul in tijts ter handt komen &
tot contentement dienen waer in ul voorder kan dinst doen
gelieft liberlijk te commandeeren terwijlen
